{"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/Mockable\/documentation\/Mockable\/Mockable()"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/Mockable\/documentation\/Mockable"]]},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"text":"@attached","kind":"attribute"},{"text":"(peer, names: prefixed(Mock)) ","kind":"text"},{"text":"macro","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Mockable","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"()","kind":"text"}]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Overview","level":2,"anchor":"overview","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The generated implementation is named with a “Mock” prefix followed by the protocol name.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"By default, the generated code is enclosed in an ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"#if MOCKING"},{"text":" condition, ensuring it is only accessible","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"in modules where the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"MOCKING"},{"text":" compile-time condition is set.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Example usage:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["@Mockable","protocol UserService {","    func get(id: UUID) -> User","    func remove(id: UUID) throws","}","","var mockUserService: MockUserService","","func test() {","    let error: UserError = .invalidId","    let mockUser = User(id: UUID())","","    given(mockUserService)","        .get(id: .any).willReturn(mockUser)","        .remove(id: .any).willThrow(error)","","    try await loginService.login()","","    verify(mockUserService)","        .get(id: .value(mockUser.id)).called(count: .once)","        .remove(id: .any).called(count: .never)","}"],"type":"codeListing"}]}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"sections":[],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A peer macro that generates a mock implementation for the protocol it is attached to."}],"kind":"symbol","metadata":{"roleHeading":"Macro","title":"Mockable()","role":"symbol","modules":[{"name":"Mockable"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"macro"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"Mockable"},{"kind":"text","text":"()"}],"externalID":"s:8MockableAAyycfm","symbolKind":"macro"},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/mockable\/mockable()"]}],"references":{"doc://Mockable/documentation/Mockable":{"kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/Mockable\/documentation\/Mockable","title":"Mockable","url":"\/documentation\/mockable","abstract":[{"text":"A macro driven testing framework that provides automatic mock implementations for your protocols. It offers an intuitive declarative syntax that simplifies the process of mocking services in unit tests.","type":"text"}],"type":"topic","role":"collection"},"doc://Mockable/documentation/Mockable/Mockable()":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A peer macro that generates a mock implementation for the protocol it is attached to."}],"role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/mockable\/mockable()","kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"macro","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Mockable","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"()","kind":"text"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/Mockable\/documentation\/Mockable\/Mockable()","type":"topic","title":"Mockable()"}}}